The Daily Mix: Arch Rival Roller Derby

Host/producer Sarah Thompson speaks with Jessica Cooke, founder of Yuppy Puppies Forever Pet Rescue. The St. Louis-area business owner and pet advocate saw a heartbreaking need  pets left behind when their owners passed away  and started Yuppy Puppies Forever. The nonprofit is dedicated to giving orphaned pets a second chance at love and family. Jessica shares the organizations mission, work and how theyre meeting a growing need to give pets hope and new beginnings. Learn more at https://yuppypuppyspa.com/yp-rescues

Host Sarah Bernard chats with Michelle Tucker, ceo of United Way about three organizations that benefit from the United Way's campaign: Catholic Charities, St. Louis Area Foodbank and The Red Cross.

Host Todd Blackstock discusses the Powder Valley Nature Conservation Center with Manager Scoot Sarantakis and Naturalist Matthew Cavanaugh. Also, Blackstock chats with Al Canal, former comedian and entertainment director of The Wildey Theatre in Edwardsville about the history and renovation of the historic architecture and a few upcoming shows
